                        "name": "3.B.2 Average number of beds in health resort hospital and health resort sanatoria",
                      
                        "goal": "Goal 3. Good health and well-being",
                      
                        "priority": "Improving the quality and availability of healthcare infrastructure",
                      
                        "definition": "Average number of beds in spa hospitals and spa sanatoriums.",
                      
                        "unit": "pieces",
                      
                        "dimensions": "total",
                      
                        "methodology": "The average number of beds is the sum of the number of beds as of the end of each month divided by 12, i.e. the number of months in a year. A spa hospital is a spa treatment facility whose tasks include providing a patient who has been referred for spa treatment or spa rehabilitation with: 1) 24-hour health care services in inpatient conditions; 2) 24-hour medical and nursing care; 3) procedures specified in the treatment program; 4) use of natural medicinal resources and spa treatment facilities; 5) health education. A spa sanatorium is a spa treatment facility. The tasks of a sanatorium include providing a patient who has been referred for spa treatment or spa rehabilitation with: 1) 24-hour health care services in inpatient conditions; 2) medical care and 24-hour nursing care; 3) procedures specified in the treatment program; 4) preventive services; 5) health education.",
                      
                        "source": "Statistics Poland",
                      
                        "availability": "Annual data, since 2010",
                      
